reviewText: This was fantastic, showing how he turned a sick New York City into an up to date place.  If he can do that I think he may be able to get our country straightened out.

The DVD is definitely a pro-Trump "documentary."  Does not discuss his lawsuits or his shenanigans or his fraud.  A quick shallow over-view of his life and times.  Good enough for those who would vote for him no matter what.
Very good documentary, should be seen by everyone!

What an eye opener to get an understanding as to the thinking that makes Donald Trump.  Surprised at what is an Amazing Man.  Amazing Parents had to be a large part of the making of the sincerity and honesty this man exudes.

Whether you like him or not, it is a good documentary on the current Republican candidate to learn of his early years, what formed him, what drives him and to see that his current public persona is the same as it has always been.

Chronicles the life of Donald Trump in flashbacks and where he was at the time the product was produced. Shares his youth which includes his church attendance, his schooling, and his entrance into the real estate business that his father was in as well.

He gains success with assistance from tax adjustments. From there he ventures into casinos and even an airline. He appears in TV and movies. Then he has some failings. Insightful, includes TV interviews of himself and others.
I love it.  I am impressed with Donald Trump.  It was well done by the producer but it needs more info about Trump's parents.

Donald John Trump was born in Queens, New York City, June 14, 1946. He is a real estate developer. His father loaned him a million dollars, which he turned into a ten billion dollar empire. He heads the Trump Organization, which has erected buildings like Trump Tower in Manhattan. Trump owns golf courses and has authored best-selling books like "The Art Of The Deal." He is media-savy and had a hit TV show called "The Apprentice." Trump has 5 kids, 3 sons and 2 daughters, by 3 wives. His wives are Ivana, Marla and Melania. Melania was born in Yugoslavia in 1970. Donald Trump announced he was running for president of the United States on June 16, 2015.
If your a trump supporter, skip this one. The History Channel continuously insults Donald Trump and his supporters. FAKE NEWS. MAGA!!!!!

As a black person. this was informative. It explained a lot. His father respect. Trump got lucky, and he knows how to use every situation to his advantage. He's not afraid of failing, because its not his money,he doesn't care what people say because in his mind only what he want matters. success is getting up one time more then you fall. God help us. Can anyone say "House of Cards", the series
If you haven't seen the Trumps early campaigns now is the time to catch up.
Bought this as a gag gift

Very well done with many video clips that helped to give a much better understanding of the life, and mindset of Donald Trump. There were several times he was asked about being the president, and his answers seemed almost prophetic because it was several decades ago!
Says quite a bit about the beginning of the man -- good and bad.  It shows his humanity in some of the mistakes he made, but also his genius.

Excellent documentary.  I was particularly surprised that his family pastor was Dr. Norman Vincent Peale, the author of The Power of Positive Thinking.  I am not a great fan of Trump in general, there is a lot to be critical of, but there is no denying the man has left an incredible legacy.  He is known for fixing up broken down areas and structures, or building amazing high end properties from nothing.  I am an independent voter in search of both good and bad views of each candidate and I struggle to find anything of substance that Hillary has done for others.  Nothing.  A lot of promises, a lot of legal maneuvers to avoid prosecution, but no substance.  Both candidates are greatly flawed.  But after seeing this I am convinced this man is capable of fixing our broken federal government.
